          <title>Fertilization Mechanism: Scientists Uncover Lock-and-Key Process in Vertebrates</title>
          <description><![CDATA[New research by scientists in Austria reveals how fertilization works across the animal kingdom, from fish to humans. A team of researchers discovered a lock-and-key mechanism involving three proteins on the sperm that unlocks the egg, allowing attachment and potentially leading to new birth control methods and infertility treatments.]]></description>
